<p>In contemporary education, <b>mathematics education</b> is the practice of <a href="Teaching" title="Teaching" class="mw-redirect">teaching</a> and <a href="Learning" title="Learning">learning</a> <a href="Mathematics" title="Mathematics">mathematics</a>, along with the associated scholarly <a href="Research" title="Research">research</a>.</p>
<p>Researchers in mathematics education are primarily concerned with the tools, methods and approaches that facilitate practice or the study of practice. However <a href="List_of_scientific_journals_in_mathematics_education" title="List of scientific journals in mathematics education" class="mw-redirect">mathematics education research</a>, known on the continent of Europe as the <a href="Didactics" title="Didactics" class="mw-redirect">didactics</a> or <a href="Pedagogy" title="Pedagogy">pedagogy</a> of mathematics, has developed into an extensive field of study, with its own concepts, theories, methods, national and international organisations, conferences and literature. This article describes some of the history, influences and recent controversies.</p>
